build_faultmodel:

 [-H]                                  Help Text
 [-h]                                  Help Text
 [-CELLAWAREFAULTPATH <path>]          Use Fault Rules from Cell Aware Fault Rule Path
 [-COREMIGRATIONPATH <path>]           Path of Core Migration Directories
 [-FAULTPATH <path>]                   Use Fault Rules from Fault Rule Path
 [-LOG no|all|summary|nosummary] (all) Customize Data Written to Log
 [-LOGCOMPRESS yes|no] (no)            Compress the log file
 [-LOGFILE <outfilename>]              Write to specified log file
 [-STDOUT no|all|summary|nosummary] (all) Customize Data Written to STDOUT
  -WORKDIR <string>                    Working Directory
 [-cellinternal no|yes] (no)           Cell Internal Fault Model (Fault Primitives in the Technology Cells)
 [-excludedynamicscanenable no|testmode|global] (testmode) Exclude Dynamic Scan Enable Faults
 [-excludedynamicsetreset no|testmode|global] (testmode) Exclude Dynamic Set/Reset Faults
 [-excludedynamictestconstraint no|testmode] (testmode) Exclude Dynamic Test Constraint Faults
 [-excludedynamictestmode <string>]    Test Mode to use for dynamic fault ignore analysis
 [-faultrulefile STDIN|<infilename>[,STDIN|<infilename>]...] Use Fault Rules from Fault Rule File
 [-help <string>]                      Help Facility
 [-hiertestupdate no|yes] (no)         Hierarchical Test Chip Fault Statistics Update
 [-identifyptab yes|no] (yes)          Identify 'Possibly Testable at Best' Faults
 [-ignoredfaultstatistics no|yes] (Conditional Default) Global Fault Statistics Using Ignored Fault Counts
 [-includedynamic yes|no] (yes)        Include Dynamic Faults
 [-maxdefectsize <decimal 0.000 to 1000000.000>] (1000000.000) Maximum delay defect size to include a defect in Cell Aware Fault Model
 [-messagecount <string>]              Limit Messages for Specified Message Id (e.g., messagecount=XXX-710=3).
 [-messagecounteach <integer>]         Default Limit for Each Message.
 [-messagecounteachseverity all|excludeinfo] (all) Level of severity for which messages are to be suppressed as per messagecounteach
 [-mindefectsize <decimal 0.000 to 1000000.000>] (0.000) Minimum delay defect size to include a defect in Cell Aware Fault Model
 [-stoponsyntaxerror no|yes] (yes)     Stop run on syntax/semantic error(s) in fault rule file(s)

